```json
{
  "application": "3D-RetinaNet",
  "software": [
    "Python 3",
    "virtualenv",
    "torch",
    "torchvision",
    "torchaudio",
    "tensorflow",
    "tensorboard",
    "tensorboardx",
    "numpy",
    "scipy",
    "pandas",
    "matplotlib"
  ],
  "resources": {
    "gpu": "v100:4",
    "cpu": "3",
    "memory": "12G",
    "time": "0-23:00:00"
  }
}
```

This script is running the 3D-RetinaNet application, a deep learning model for object detection in 3D videos. It utilizes various software including Python 3, virtualenv, PyTorch, Tensorflow, and several other Python libraries. It requires significant resources including 4 v100 GPUs, 3 CPUs, 12 GB of memory, and a time limit of 23 hours. The script runs on Compute Canada infrastructure, a high-performance computing environment.
